Package org.multigraph

Interface Summary
Data.Iterator Objects adhering to the Data.Iterator interface act as iterators for stepping through rows from a Data object.
Data.ReadyHandler Objects adhering to the Data.ReadyHandler interface can be registered with a Data object via its onReady() method; the registered object's dataReady() method will be called whenever new data is available in the Data object.
 

Class Summary
Data This is the (abstract) superclass for classes that Multigraph uses for loading, storing, and managing data to be plotted.
DataMeasure A DataMeasure object stores a "measure" which reprents a (directed) distance along a number line.
DataValue A DataValue represents a data value that can be plotted along a real number line.
DataVariable A DataVariable object stores the metadata associated with a particular variable in a Data object.
DatetimeMeasure A DatetimeMeasure stores a length of time, represented in terms of a "unit" and a "measure".
DatetimeValue DatetimeValue is the DataValue implementation for the DATETIME data type (DataValue.Type.DATETIME).
NumberMeasure A NumberMeasure stores a measure of length (and direction) along a number axis.
NumberValue NumberValue is the DataValue implementation for the NUMBER data type (DataValue.Type.NUMBER).
 

Enum Summary
DataValue.Type The DataValue.Type enum contains constants representing the various types of DataValue possible in Multigraph; it has one constant for each DataValue subclass.
DatetimeMeasure.Unit A DatetimeMeasure.Unit represents a field for calendar computations --- year, month, day, hour, etc.
